46:37.362 --> 46:48.212
Without the two great American books, I would, well, in terms of eminence, I would say Leaves of Grass, and I would say if it has any rival, it has to be Moby Dick.

46:49.113 --> 46:52.256
And you would call them our epics?

46:52.316 --> 47:00.623
Leaves of Grass, well, Song of Myself, the heart of the first Leaves of Grass, what eventually gets to be called Song of Myself,

47:01.126 --> 47:09.500
is in a way the national epic, but Leaves of Grass as a composite is certainly the national epic.

47:09.760 --> 47:14.868
A kind of dark anti-epic, as it were.

47:16.351 --> 47:20.377
Moby Dick.

47:20.738 --> 47:21.379
Hi, Gene.

47:22.321 --> 47:23.663
Okay.

47:23.783 --> 47:25.184
Hello, dear.

47:25.224 --> 47:26.686
I won't keep you too much.

47:26.946 --> 47:33.754
Again, I have the books, but I do... You were talking about that Leaves of Grass and Moby Dick.

47:33.795 --> 47:34.315
Exactly.

47:34.435 --> 47:35.857
There's the epics.

47:37.399 --> 47:40.122
I can't really think of a third one.

47:40.202 --> 47:45.368
